rComments: This class had weekly journal entries, a preliminary report, a presentation, a paper, and an evaluation by your supervisor. I enjoyed the practical aspect of my internship, but Crete took away from the experience. Not only did he not help me find a place to do my internship, but he didn't provide feedback for any assignments.
His lectures are dry and he doesn't provide any rubrics for bad grades given. It's very unfortunate that he's in charge of internships because he takes away from the quality of the experience.

encourages you to meet with him to go over assignments but neither him or TAs provide feedback. Your journal entries are evaluated on length and you will likely not get more than 4/5. if you do everything you're supposed to you'll get an 85% but you cant find out why/what you need to do to get higher cause no one knows why you got the mark you did

Not helpful in the slightest. He doesn't mark any of your work himself so when you meet with him to ask why he gave you a horrible mark, he literally can't tell you because he didn't even read your paper. He doesn't believe that anyone deserves a 100%, and 85% seems to be the best mark he's ever heard of. The internship class itself is not hard.
